<p>St. Louis's diverse neighborhoods each present unique considerations for solar and HVAC installations. The Central West End and Clayton areas feature many historic homes with mature tree coverage, requiring careful solar site assessment and potentially specialized HVAC solutions for older building layouts. These upscale neighborhoods often have higher property values that can better accommodate premium solar and HVAC investments.</p>

<p>South St. Louis neighborhoods like Tower Grove and Benton Park consist largely of brick homes built in the early 1900s, which may require HVAC system modifications to work with existing ductwork or the addition of ductless mini-split systems. The Delmar Loop and University City areas attract environmentally conscious residents who are often early adopters of solar technology. North County areas like Florissant and Hazelwood typically feature newer construction with more standard roof orientations suitable for solar installations and modern HVAC infrastructure.</p>

